### Enterprise Error Handling

Here is the code updated with try-catch blocks and explicit validation logic to handle edge cases gracefully:

```typescript
'use server';
export async function createPostSafe(formData) {
  try {
    const title = formData.get('title');
    if (!title) throw new Error('Title required');
    await db.post.create({ data: { title } });
    revalidatePath('/posts');
    return { success: true };
  } catch (e) {
    return { success: false, error: e.message };
  }
}
```

